ieee8021BridgePEMib.name: ieee8021BridgePEMib

revisions.description: Initial version published as part of IEEE Std. 802.1BR-2012

ieee8021BridgePEMib.contactinfo: WG-URL: http:////www.ieee802.org/1/ WG-EMail: stds-802-1-L@IEEE.ORG Contact: Tony Jeffree Postal: C/O IEEE 802.1 Working Group IEEE Standards Association 445 Hoes Lane Piscataway NJ 08854 USA E-mail: stds-802-1-L@IEEE.ORG
ieee8021BridgePEMib.description: The PE MIB module for managing devices that support Bridge Port Extension. Unless otherwise indicated, the references in this MIB module are to IEEE Std 802.1BR-2012. Copyright (C) IEEE. This version of this MIB module is part of IEEE 802.1BR-2012; see the specification itself for full legal notices.

IEEE802BridgePEEChannelIDTC.name: IEEE802BridgePEEChannelIDTC
IEEE802BridgePEEChannelIDTC.description: Textual convention of an E-Channel Identifier.

IEEE802BridgePETrafficClassValueTC.name: IEEE802BridgePETrafficClassValueTC
IEEE802BridgePETrafficClassValueTC.description: Indicates a traffic class. Values 0-7 correspond to traffic classes.

IEEE802BridgePETrafficSelectionAlgorithm.name: IEEE802BridgePETrafficSelectionAlgorithmTC
IEEE802BridgePETrafficSelectionAlgorithm.description: Indicates the Traffic Selection Algorithm 0: Strict Priority 1: Credit-based shaper 2: Enhanced transmission selection 3-254: Reserved for furture standardization 255: Vendor specific

IEEE802BridgePETrafficClassBandwidthValu.name: IEEE802BridgePETrafficClassBandwidthValue
IEEE802BridgePETrafficClassBandwidthValu.description: Indicates the bandwidth in percent assigned to a traffic class.

ieee8021BridgePEPortTable.name: ieee8021BridgePEPortTable
ieee8021BridgePEPortTable.description: A table that contains per port information related to Port Extension. A row is created in this table for any port on a Controlling Bridge that is extended using Port Extension, including those ports that provide communication to the Port Extenders themselves.

ieee8021BridgePEPortEntry.name: ieee8021BridgePEPortEntry
ieee8021BridgePEPortEntry.description: A list of per port Port Extension objects.

ieee8021BridgePEPortComponentId.name: ieee8021BridgePEPortComponentId
ieee8021BridgePEPortComponentId.description: The component identifier is used to distinguish between the multiple virtual bridge instances within a PBB. In simple situations where there is only a single component the default value is 1.

ieee8021BridgePEPort.name: ieee8021BridgePEPort
ieee8021BridgePEPort.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains bridge management information.

ieee8021BridgePEPortType.name: ieee8021BridgePEPortType
ieee8021BridgePEPortType.description: The operational mode of a port participating in Port Exension. The enumerated values are: pepCascade - the port is operating as a Cascade port pepUpstream - the port is operating as an Upstream port pepExtended - the port is operating as an Extended port

ieee8021BridgePEPortUpstreamCSPAddress.name: ieee8021BridgePEPortUpstreamCSPAddress
ieee8021BridgePEPortUpstreamCSPAddress.description: The MAC address used for communication of the PE CSP protocol of the device connected to the upstream port of the Port Extender (which may be the Controlling Bridge or an upstream Port Extender). This provides the hierarchal relationship in a cascade of Port Extenders

ieee8021BridgePEPortEcid.name: ieee8021BridgePEPortEcid
ieee8021BridgePEPortEcid.description: The default ECID assigend to this port and the port on the Port Extender to which this port corresponds.

ieee8021BridgePEPortNumber.name: ieee8021BridgePEPortNumber
ieee8021BridgePEPortNumber.description: The Port number on the of the Port on the Port Extender, or zero for the Upstream Port.

ieee8021BridgePECounterDiscontinuityTime.name: ieee8021BridgePECounterDiscontinuityTime
ieee8021BridgePECounterDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which any one or more of the counters in this conceptaul row suffered a discontinuity. The relevant counters are the specific instances associated with this conceptual row of any Counter32 or Counter64 object. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last re-initialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrqErrorsBridge.name: ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrqErrorsBridge
ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrqErrorsBridge.description: The number of PE CSP flow control overflow errors that have occured for requests on the Bridge.

ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrspErrorsBridge.name: ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrspErrorsBridge
ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrspErrorsBridge.description: The number of PE CSP flow control overflow errors that have occured for responses on the Bridge.

ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrqErrorsPE.name: ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrqErrorsPE
ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrqErrorsPE.description: The number of PE CSP flow control overflow errors that have occured for requests on the Port Extender.

ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrspErrorsPE.name: ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrspErrorsPE
ieee8021BridgePEPortRxrspErrorsPE.description: The number of PE CSP flow control overflow errors that have occured for responses on the Port Extender.

ieee8021BridgePEPCP.name: ieee8021BridgePEPCP
ieee8021BridgePEPCP.description: Indicates whether the Port Exender supports modification of the priority code point table (true) or not (false).

ieee8021BridgePEROW.name: ieee8021BridgePEROW
ieee8021BridgePEROW.description: Indicates whether the Port Extender supports rows in the PCP table in addition to the 8P0D row (true)or not (false).

ieee8021BridgePEDEI.name: ieee8021BridgePEDEI
ieee8021BridgePEDEI.description: Indicates whether the Port Extender supports encoding of the Drop Eligible Indicatior (true) or not (false).

ieee8021BridgePECN.name: ieee8021BridgePECN
ieee8021BridgePECN.description: Indicates whether the Port Extender supports Congestion Notification (true) or not (false).

ieee8021BridgePEPFC.name: ieee8021BridgePEPFC
ieee8021BridgePEPFC.description: Indicates whether the Port Extender supports Priority-based flow control(true) or not (false).

ieee8021BridgePEExtPortEChannelsSupporte.name: ieee8021BridgePEExtPortEChannelsSupported
ieee8021BridgePEExtPortEChannelsSupporte.description: Indicates the number of Extended Port E-channels supported by the Port Extender.

ieee8021BridgePERemoteRepEChannelsSuppor.name: ieee8021BridgePERemoteRepEChannelsSupported
ieee8021BridgePERemoteRepEChannelsSuppor.description: Indicates the number of Remote Replication E-channels supported by the Port Extender.

ieee8021BridgePETCsSupported.name: ieee8021BridgePETCsSupported
ieee8021BridgePETCsSupported.description: Indicates the number of traffic clasees supported by the Port Extender.

ieee8021BridgePEUtVLANsSupported.name: ieee8021BridgePEUtVLANsSupported
ieee8021BridgePEUtVLANsSupported.description: Indicates the number of untagged VLANs supported by the Port Extender.

ieee8021BridgePERemoteReplicationTable.name: ieee8021BridgePERemoteReplicationTable
ieee8021BridgePERemoteReplicationTable.description: A table that contains one row for each Remote Replication entry in the filtering database.

ieee8021BridgePERemoteReplicationEntry.name: ieee8021BridgePERemoteReplicationEntry
ieee8021BridgePERemoteReplicationEntry.description: A list of Remote Replication objects.

ieee8021BridgePERREcid.name: ieee8021BridgePERREcid
ieee8021BridgePERREcid.description: The ECID assigend to this Remote Replication filtering entry.

ieee8021BridgePERRPortMap.name: ieee8021BridgePERRPortMap
ieee8021BridgePERRPortMap.description: The list of ports to which a frame is to be replicated.

ieee8021BridgePEETSTable.name: ieee8021BridgePEETSTable
ieee8021BridgePEETSTable.description: A table that contains per port information related to Enhanced Transmission Selection. A row is created in this table for any port on a Controlling Bridge that corresponds to a Cascade Port. These objects refer to the ETS configuration of the attached Upstream Port

ieee8021BridgePEETSEntry.name: ieee8021BridgePEETSEntry
ieee8021BridgePEETSEntry.description: A list of per Cascade Port ETS objects.

ieee8021BridgePEETSTrafficClass.name: ieee8021BridgePEETSTrafficClass
ieee8021BridgePEETSTrafficClass.description: Indicates the traffic class to which this bandwidth applies

ieee8021BridgePEETSTrafficSelectionAlgor.name: ieee8021BridgePEETSTrafficSelectionAlgorthm
ieee8021BridgePEETSTrafficSelectionAlgor.description: Inticates the Traffic Selection Algorthm assigned to this traffic class

ieee8021BridgePEETSBandwidth.name: ieee8021BridgePEETSBandwidth
ieee8021BridgePEETSBandwidth.description: Indicates the bandwidth assigned to this traffic class.

ieee8021BridgePEGroup.name: ieee8021BridgePEGroup
ieee8021BridgePEGroup.description: The collection of objects used to represent Port Extension management objects.

ieee8021BridgePECompliance.name: ieee8021BridgePECompliance
ieee8021BridgePECompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices supporting PE as defined in IEEE 802.1BR.
